resentations of culture, these movies are indebted to religious notions of divination and revelation. Exploring the format of "film as revelation," Meyer unpacks the affinity between cinematic and popular Christian modes of looking and showcases the transgressive potential haunting figurations of the occult. In this brilliant study, Meyer offers a deep, conceptually innovative analysis of the role of visual culture within the politics and aesthetics of religious world making.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aMotion picture industryzGhanay20th century. 0aMotion picturesxReligious aspectsxPentacostalism. 0aMotion picturesxSocial aspectszGhana. 0aVideo recordings industryzGhanay20th century. 0aVideo recordingsxReligious aspectsxPentacostalism. 0aVideo recordingsxSocial aspectszGhana. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  achristian modes of looking.  achristian revelation.  achristianity in ghana.  adivination.  afilm and cinema in ghana.  afilm as revelation.  aghanaian film industry.  aghanaian filmmakers.  aghanaian politics.  aghanaian religion.  alate 20th century film and cinema.  aoccult in film.  aoccultism.  apopular filmmaking in ghana.  areligious aesthetics in film.  areligious aesthetics in ghanaian film.  arevelation.  avisual culture in ghana.  aworld religions.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015z97831106211120 cprintz978052028767940uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052096265140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520962651423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520962651/original  a978-3-11-062111-2  University of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB